author: COMSOL
description: This example shows hydrocarbon dehalogenation as it occurs in a tortuous microreactor. The reactants are transported from the fluid bulk to the catalytic surfaces at the reactor walls, where they react. Both a space-independent model, analyzing two competing reactions using the Reaction Engineering interface, and a space-dependent model, that includes fluid flow and mass transport, are set up and solved.
